      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Encoder-Decoder Training Objective"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Given a source sequence "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "X = x_1, \\ldots, x_m"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and a target sequence "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "Y = y_1, \\ldots, y_n"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the model is trained to maximise:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockMath",
        "attrs": {
          "latex": "\\log P(Y \\mid X) = \\sum_{t=1}^{n} \\log P(y_t \\mid y_1, \\ldots, y_{t-1}, X)"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The decoder is autoregressive: it generates one token at a time, conditioning on all previously generated tokens "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "and"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " the full source via cross-attention. During training the true target tokens are fed in (\"teacher forcing\"); at inference the model's own predictions are fed back in."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Seq2Seq with Hugging Face"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "T5 (\"Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer\") frames every NLP task as a seq2seq problem by prepending a task prefix to the input."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from transformers import T5ForConditionalGeneration, T5Tokenizer\n\nmodel_name = \"t5-small\"\ntokenizer = T5Tokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\nmodel = T5ForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(model_name)\n\n# Translation: prefix tells T5 which task to perform\ninputs = tokenizer(\n    \"translate English to French: The cat is sleeping.\",\n    return_tensors=\"pt\",\n)\noutput_ids = model.generate(**inputs, max_new_tokens=50)\nprint(tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0], skip_special_tokens=True))\n# Le chat dort.\n\n# Summarisation: same model, different prefix\ninputs = tokenizer(\n    \"summarize: The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog \"\n    \"and then ran off into the sunset.\",\n    return_tensors=\"pt\",\n)\noutput_ids = model.generate(**inputs, max_new_tokens=30)\nprint(tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0], skip_special_tokens=True))\n# the fox jumped over the lazy dog."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Decoding: Beam Search for Seq2Seq"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For seq2seq tasks with a definite correct answer (translation, summarisation), "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "beam search"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the standard decoding strategy. It maintains B candidate sequences (\"beams\") and keeps the B highest-scoring ones at each step. Greedy decoding is beam search with B=1."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from transformers import MarianMTModel, MarianTokenizer\n\n# Helsinki-NLP models are encoder-decoder specifically for translation\nmodel_name = \"Helsinki-NLP/opus-mt-fr-en\"\ntokenizer = MarianTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\nmodel = MarianMTModel.from_pretrained(model_name)\n\nsrc = [\"Le chat dort sur le tapis.\", \"Le chien mange.\"]\ntokenized = tokenizer(src, return_tensors=\"pt\", padding=True)\n\ntranslated = model.generate(\n    **tokenized,\n    num_beams=4,           # beam width — explore 4 candidates\n    early_stopping=True,   # stop when all beams reach EOS\n    max_length=50,\n)\nfor t in translated:\n    print(tokenizer.decode(t, skip_special_tokens=True))\n# The cat sleeps on the rug.\n# The dog eats."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
